Police have made a major bust at a Devland scrapyard near Soweto. The raid was a joint operation between the SAPS, JMPD, and Eskom. eNCA speaks to Eskom Head of security, Karen Pillay. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have made a major bust at a Devland scrapyard near Soweto. READ: Major cable theft bust in Tshwane Piles of copper cables were confiscated during a joint raid between the South African Police Service, Johannesburg Metro Police Department and Eskom. The cables were stolen from Transnet Freight Rail, Prasa, Eskom and City Power.